        <font size='4'><b>OLIVER TRUMBLE WARMS UP TO VACATION</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20090129.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Audrey Smythe-Wei<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, January 29, 2009</b> &mdash;
    Years of hard work deserve some relaxation. And former mayor Oliver Trumble recently got a head start on his big vacation. <br><br>Trumble returned just a few days ago from <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=7">Okalani Island</a>, where he and his family took in a whole lot of tropical recreation and beaming sunrays. <br><br>&quot;It was a great trip,&quot; said Trumble, &quot;and it was really nice to spend some time with my family, especially in the warmer weather.&quot;<br><br>&quot;We got to do some <a href="http://millsberry.com/peabody_park/pond/">fishing</a> while we were out there, and I gave my kids surfing lessons,&quot; he added. <br><br>With more than a weeks&#039; break from the colder weather, the former mayor had to adapt his favorite winter pastimes to his tropical surroundings.<br>
<br>
&quot;I was able to make a sled out of driftwood and palm leaves. And I built a <a href="http://millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=7">sandman</a> instead of a snowman, with a stick for the nose and seashells for eyes,&quot; he said smiling.<br><br>&quot;Making sand angels was fun too, but they get washed away pretty quickly by the surf. You have to enjoy them fast,&quot; he laughed. <br><br>After Trumble&#039;s years of hard work on behalf of the citizens of Millsberry, this vacation came at the perfect time, providing some much-needed rest. <br><br>&quot;It was good, getting to put my feet up for a little while,&quot; he said. <br><br>&quot;Millsberry is in great hands with new mayor, Douglas Wright, so I can sit back and relax. I do plan on continuing to help out around the city when I can,&quot; he added. <br><br>With so much free time on his hands, he&#039;ll also have to figure out how to keep himself occupied when not pitching in around town. <br><br>&quot;I&#039;m planning on taking up some new hobbies,&quot; said Oliver, &quot;and learning a foreign language or two.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Rock climbing would be a lot of fun. I could see myself getting into rock climbing. I&#039;ve never been afraid of heights, so that shouldn&#039;t be a problem,&quot; he laughed.<br><br>No matter what Oliver Trumble does from here on out, he&#039;s sure to enjoy himself.  
    </div>

